| style="font-size: 140%; padding: 0.25em 0.9em;" | <div><center>'''Remember your manners'''</center></div>
|-
| <p style="text-align: center;">'''We recommend that before you create your question, you read these tips to editing on the Edible Scratch Wiki.'''</p>
*Sign your posts with four tildes (<nowiki>~~~~</nowiki>) after your post.
*To do various text formatting, follow the following rules, rather than using any other text-editing methods:
**Make text '''bold''' with <nowiki>'''text'''</nowiki>.
**Make text ''italics'' with <nowiki>''text''</nowiki>.
**Make text '''''bold and italics''''' with <nowiki>'''''text'''''</nowiki>.
**Make a [http://scratch.mit.edu link to a page outside of this wiki] with <nowiki>[http://www.example.com link text] or {{plain link|1=http://www.example.com|2=link text}} if you don't want the </nowiki>[[File:Link icon.png]] symbol to appear (remember http:// prefix).
**Make a [[Scratch Wiki|link to an article on this wiki]] with <nowiki>[[Page name]]</nowiki> or <nowiki>[[Page name|Link text]]</nowiki>.
**Make a [[Wikipedia:Scratch (programming language)|link to a Wikipedia article]] with <nowiki>[[Wikipedia:Page name]] or [[Wikipedia:Page name|Link text]]</nowiki>.
**Indent a paragraph by putting a colon (:) before it.
**For more, see [[Help:Formatting|the help page on formatting]].
*Put new text under old text.
*Always remember to be polite and respectful, [[Scratch Wiki:Assume Good Faith|assume good faith]], and be welcoming, while following the [http://scratch.mit.edu/community_guidelines Scratch Community Guidelines].
<!-- *When creating a new post, mark it as {{not done}} by putting {{t|not done}} at the top. Once the conversation has been resolved, replace it with {{t|done}} (producing {{done}}). -->
